CP%29&amp;author=RE+Hintze&amp;author=A+Adler&amp;author=W+Veltzke&amp;publication_year=1997&amp;journal=Endoscopy&amp;pages=182-187&amp;doi=10.1055%2Fs-2007-1004160&amp;pmid=9201467">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">3.</div><div id="r3" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Irie H, Honda H, Tajima T, et al. Optimal MR cholangiopancreatographic sequence and its clinical application. <em>Radiology</em> 1998;206:379-387.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiology.206.2.9457189">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9457189/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Optimal+MR+cholangiopancreatographic+sequence+and+its+clinical+application&amp;author=H+Irie&amp;author=H+Honda&amp;author=T+Tajima&amp;publication_year=1998&amp;journal=Radiology&amp;pages=379-387&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiology.206.2.9457189&amp;pmid=9457189">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">4.</div><div id="r4" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Mortelé KJ, Rocha TC, Streeter JL, et al. Multimodality imaging of pancreatic and biliary congenital anomalies. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2006;26(3):715–731.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.263055164">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16702450/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Multimodality+imaging+of+pancreatic+and+biliary+congenital+anomalies&amp;author=KJ+Mortel%C3%A9&amp;author=TC+Rocha&amp;author=JL+Streeter&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=715-731&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.263055164&amp;pmid=16702450">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">5.</div><div id="r5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Sureka B, Bansal K, Patidar Y, et al. Magnetic resonance cholangiographic evaluation of intrahepatic and extrahepatic bile duct variations. <em>Indian J Radiol Imaging</em> 2016;26:22-32.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.4103/0971-3026.178283">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27081220/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Magnetic+resonance+cholangiographic+evaluation+of+intrahepatic+and+extrahepatic+bile+duct+variations&amp;author=B+Sureka&amp;author=K+Bansal&amp;author=Y+Patidar&amp;publication_year=2016&amp;journal=Indian+J+Radiol+Imaging&amp;pages=22-32&amp;doi=10.4103%2F0971-3026.178283&amp;pmid=27081220">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
